# History: ci-hygiene-and-validation-gates

This file preserves the full original content of the skills merged into
`ci-hygiene-and-validation-gates`.

## v1.3.0 (2026-06-20)

**What changed:** Added **Pattern 6 — already-wired issue: justfile discoverability comment** to
`## When to Use`, `## Verified Workflow` (new subsection with 5-step workflow), `## Failed Attempts`
(two new rows for Pattern 6), and `## Verified On` (ProjectHermes issue #496 / branch
`496-auto-impl`). Bumped `version` 1.2.0 → 1.3.0 (MINOR — additive pattern), `date` →
2026-06-20, added tags `already-wired`, `discoverability-comment`, `prior-pr-completed`,
`justfile-cross-reference`. Also corrected the Overview Patterns field to enumerate all 5+6
patterns explicitly.

**Why:** Issue #496 in ProjectHermes asked to wire `scripts/check_dep_sync.py` into a CI lint job.
Investigation revealed the `deps-version-sync` CI job already existed in
`.github/workflows/_required.yml` (added by PR #594 / commit `3ee26ae`), running unconditionally
on every `pull_request` to `main`. The correct resolution was NOT to re-wire or duplicate the
CI step but to insert a single cross-reference comment in `justfile` above the `dep-check`
recipe. This "already-wired issue → discoverability comment" pattern recurs whenever a prior PR
quietly closed the CI gap and the issue was not updated. Searchers for "wire X into CI" / "already
exists in CI" / "justfile cross-reference" should land on this skill.

