## v1.1.0 (2026-06-12)

**What changed:** Added **Pattern 4 — detect & fix a dead required gate** to
`## Verified Workflow` (with a Quick Reference two-sided verification block), five
new `## Failed Attempts` rows, a `## Results & Parameters` subsection for the
dead-gate fix, and a `## Verified On` row (ProjectHephaestus issue #1181 / PR
#1266). Bumped `version` 1.0.0 → 1.1.0 (MINOR — additive pattern), `date` → 2026-06-12,
added tags `required-status-check`, `dead-gate`, `no-op-assertion`, `version-sync`,
`set-e`, `pinned-context`, `defense-in-depth`, `pip-install-deps`, `pixi-locked`.

**Why:** A required status check (`deps/version-sync`) computed a verdict, `echo`ed
it, and discarded it; its only `exit 1` lived behind `if [ -f VERSION ]` while the
repo has no `VERSION` file (hatch-vcs dynamic versioning) — so the gate passed for
ANY version configuration (security-theater). The context was pinned in the org
ruleset and could not be deleted (deletion bricks the merge queue), so the gate had
to be made real in-place. Searchers for "required check asserts nothing" / "dead
gate" should land on this skill alongside the existing grep/schema/stale patterns.

